<p>I am running a cronjob on Express Server. This cron job access 3rd party API and fetch some data. To make the API (Oauth v2) call I need my server's <code>baseurl</code> (not <code>hostname</code> via <code>os</code> module).</p>  <p>Since its a cronjob there is no <code>request</code> object. Is it possible to get server's <code>baseurl</code> without <code>request</code> object directly exposed.</p>